Reasoning: The paper discusses the creation of new optimization algorithms by incorporating concepts from artificial human optimization. This falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with optimization algorithms inspired by biological systems. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as it covers a broad range of topics related to intelligent systems. cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories as they cover topics related to optimization and control. Finally, cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant if the optimization algorithms are intended for use in robotics applications.
